# {{.Name}}

A Go web application built with the [HAMR framework](https://github.com/FyrmForge/hamr).

## Prerequisites

- Go {{.GoVersion}}+
- Docker (for PostgreSQL)
- [templ](https://templ.guide) CLI (`go install github.com/a-h/templ/cmd/templ@latest`)

## Quick Start

```bash
# Install dev tools (reflex, templ)
make install

# Start the database
make docker-up

# Run the server (generates templ files + live reload)
make dev
```

The server starts at [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080).

## Development

```bash
make dev            # Run dev server (live reload)
make build          # Build binary to bin/server
make test           # Run tests
make lint           # Run golangci-lint
make migrate        # Run database migrations
make db-sh          # Open pgcli shell to local dev DB
make docker-up      # Start services
make docker-down    # Stop services
```
{{- if .IncludeE2E}}

## E2E Testing

```bash
make e2e            # Run containerized E2E tests
make e2e-local      # Run against local server
make e2e-run T=Test # Run specific test
```
{{- end}}

## Project Structure

```
cmd/server/              Application entry point
cmd/migrate/             Standalone migration runner
internal/
  config/                Environment configuration
  db/                    Database + migrations
  repo/                  Data access layer
  web/                   HTTP handlers + components
static/                  CSS, JS, images
docker/                  Docker Compose
docs/                    Documentation
```

## Stack

- **Go** {{.GoVersion}} + Echo v4
- **Templ** + HTMX + Alpine.js
- **PostgreSQL**
- **HAMR Framework** — server, middleware, validation, responses
